li.p:
Because the point (-4, 6) does lie on the graph, the ordered pair x=-4, y = 6 is a solution of y = 0.5x^2 - 2. We can verify this by substituting \alert{-4} for x and \blert{6} for y:
                0.5(\alert{-4})^2 - 2 \amp= 0.5(16) - 2
                    = 8 - 2 \amp = \blert{6}

Because the point (3, 0) does not lie on the graph, the ordered pair x = 3, y = 0 is not a solution of y = 0.5x^2 - 2. We substitute \alert{3} for x and \blert{0} for y to verify this.
                0.5(\alert{3})^2 - 2 \amp= 0.5(9) - 2
                    = 4.5 - 2 \amp = 2.5 \ne \blert{0}
